Peel and chop the @red potato{2} into 2cm chunks. Pop into a #pot of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and put on high heat. When boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for ~{15-20%minutes}.

> The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

While your potato cooks, prepare the salsa. Cut the @cherry tomatoes{1} in half through the equator. Pop them in a #bowl with a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

Cut the @echalion shallot{1} in half through the root, peel and then chop into ¼cm chunks (or as small as you can!). Mix this with your tomatoes. Pick the leaves from the @tarragon{1/4} stalks in a bunch, discard the stalks and then chop the leaves. Add these to your tomatoes and shallot and mix well.

Stir the @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} and @balsamic vinegar{1%tbsp} into your salsa and add a splash of @olive oil{1%splash}. Give it a good stir and leave to one side.

Place the @flank steak{4} on a #plate and drizzle over a splash of @oil{1%splash}. Season each steak with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind}. Sprinkle over the @ground coriander{1%tsp} and then massage all of these ingredients into your steak. Wash your hands, then grate the @mature cheddar cheese{125%g} on the coarse side of your #grater.

Once your potato is cooked, drain in a #colander and allow the steam to escape for ~{2%mins}.

> This will create a drier, fluffier mash!

Mash your potato with a #potato masher{} or #fork and add your cheese, a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{splash} (if you have some!). Mix well and then add more @salt{to taste} and @black pepper{to taste}.

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil) and when it is very hot, carefully lay your steak in the pan to sear. We like our steak medium rare and cook it for ~{3-4%mins} on each side. If you like your steak well done, cook for another ~{1-2%mins} on each side. When your steak is ready allow it to rest before slicing.

Cut each steak into eight thin slices. Serve a generous amount of cheesy mash and place your steak alongside. Spoon over your tomato salsa and enjoy!